sentence: A similar example is given by the Senegalese sole (Solea senegalensis), which, when acclimated to temperatures of 26 ° C, produced a significantly higher amount of taurine, Glutamic acid, Gamma-Aminobutyric acid and glycine compared to acclimation to 12 ° C. This may mean that the aforementioned compounds aid in antioxidant defense, osmoregulatory processes, or energetic purposes at these temperatures.
